// kisi bhi ek ComputerNetwork(cn) meh bohat sari diff-diff types of cables use hoti hai,, jaise agr apn apne computernetwork( mtlb myajay Computernetwork jismeh ek laptop hai, ek mouse, ek jiofidongle, ek iphone and ek tablet hai joki aapas meh connected hai and apne-app meh ek ComputerNetwork hai) ki baat kre then apne computernetwork meh keyboard and laptopscreen aapas meh cables se connected hai, toh mtlb yeh cables kaise hai, konsi hai , enn cables ko kis naam se boltehh hai etc..etc.. apn ek ComputerNetworks meh Cables k bareh meh yaha janenge..
// diff-diff Cables ka use particularly particular devices ko connect krne k liyeh bhi hota hai, mtlb jaise apnko cpu ko printer se connect krne k liyeh coaxial-cable hi chahiyehh hoti hai aur mtlb coaxial-cable se apn cpu and printer ko connect kr sktehh hai, mtlb aur kisi Cable se enn devices k bich meh communication nhi ho sktaa.
// thus toh mtlb as per need and requirement for making communication or connection between diff devices different Cables ki jarurat hoti hai, pdti hai.

// allover different type of cables in ComputerNetwork:-
// 1.unshielded twistedpair cable (signal is in electricalform , 10BaseT , 100BaseT)
// 2.shielded twistedpair cable ( same as unshielded cables)
// 3.coaxial cable (signal is in electrical-form , 10Base2 , 10Base5)
// 4.fibre-optic cable (signal is in form of light mtlb speed is very fast , 100BaseFx)

// these cables are used in ethernet-LANs(local-area-Networks)
// enn sabhi Cables meh collision hota hai , and maximumly "n"-collisions ho sktehh hai, agr cable se "n"-devices connected hai toh.
// bandwidth of Cable mtlb uss Cable meh se apn kitni bits per second over all crossection-area transmit kr stkehh hai.
// cable ko apn medium bhi bol sktehh hai, aur mtlb boltehh bhi hai.
// Baseband-Cable mtlb voh cable jismeh ek baar meh sirf ek signal hi transfer hota hai, mtlb ekbaar meh multiple signal transfer nhi hotehh and agr hotehh hai toh phir unn signals k bich collision hoga.
// Broadband-Cable mtlb voh cable jismeh ek baar meh parralley saat-meh mutiple signals trasmit hotehh hai.
// Attentuation mtlb signal ki strength/energy low hojana, and aab voh signal jada aage move nhi krskta.
// LAN(local area network) mtlb less network of radius less than 10km.
// upar 10BaseT ka mtlb 10Mbps-bandwidth , it is Baseband-cable and T mtlb 100meter(mtlb attentuation occurs at 100meters)
//  10Base2 meh "2" ka mtlb hai 200meters
// 100Basefx meh "fx" mtlb fibre-channel-range and it is about 2km (mtlb 2km meh signal-attentuation hota hai.)
// Cables physical-layer meh use hoti hai..
// Cables fully hardware hai, mtlb enmeh koi software nhi hotehh jisseh apn Cable-meh-transmitting signal ko kahi bich meh rok sake, tok sake(whereas tokna mtlb esseh nhi hoga ki cable meh transmitting-signal ka apn mac-address, ip-address etc.. puch sake, jaan sake etc..etc..) toh allover mtlb ki Cables meh apn signal ki filtering nhi kr sktehh.

